subject: Blogging in Quikscript

messageBody:
I re-started my blog, now at <http://www.frogorbits.com/blog/>. The two most recent posts are in Quikscript, and I intend to continue this for some time. (No idea if I'll run out of things to say anytime soon; I'm not much of a diarist.)

If you're like me and would rather have a computer poll the website to see if there's anything new, the Atom feed is at <http://www.frogorbits.com/atom.xml>.

Any and all typo notices will be greatly appreciated; I'm trying to get a better feel for Read's RP, and I'm still adrift when it comes to differentiating between the THOUGHT and LOT lexical sets. My recollection of "Kevin Phillips Bong (Slightly Silly)…naught" suggests that "naught" and "thought" are in the same lexical set, but I wouldn't bet money on it.

(yes, I could look this sort of thing up; I'm trying to see if I can make better guesses without having to use a dictionary.)
